{
  "stem": "95.3",
  "chunk_idx": 18,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 130,
      "text": "They started to evacuate the Jews-- again, death marches, death camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 131,
      "text": "And he got my papers, put it aside, and he hid me in his barrack.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 132,
      "text": "And I got-- my number was 125,603 in Buchenwald, and I had a pass that I could go from the little camp to the big camp whenever I want to with that pass.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 133,
      "text": "And-- and I-- and that's what I would do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 134,
      "text": "I would go and meet my friend and my French friends during the daytime, and then go-- go and hide in his barrack.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 135,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we knew-- they knew everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 136,
      "text": "In Buchenwald, there was a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 137,
      "text": "Most people were German communists, and they were sabotaging everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 138,
      "text": "They worked in an arms factory there, and they would do great sabotage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 139,
      "text": "And they knew everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 140,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the day we were liberated, which is April 11th, 1945, we were liberated by our own people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 141,
      "text": "That morning, they-- because they smuggled arms and everything, and ammunition.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 142,
      "text": "And they cut out the wires and went into the forest, because Buchenwald is a beech wood-- that's why it's in Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 143,
      "text": "And they were surrounded by beech wood.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 144,
      "text": "And they-- because the day we were liberated, nobody was there at roll call.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 145,
      "text": "No guard-- no guards in the guard towers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 146,
      "text": "It was-- everybody fled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 147,
      "text": "All the Ger-- all the Nazis left, the SS left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 148,
      "text": "And they got them back, they got them back as prisoners.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 149,
      "text": "[AUDIO OUT]",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
